metadata.name: Lucid Dream #253
metadata.description:
Lucid Dream is our contribution to celebrate #fxhashturnsone!

 It‚Äôs our first long-form collection with shaders! Throughout the year we had the opportunity to explore and improve ourselves. Therefore, we wanted to celebrate this anniversary with a technique/medium that is new to us.

You can explore hidden textures and colors by interacting the animation with your cursor.

‚ÄúLucid dreaming is the experience of achieving conscious awareness of dreaming while still asleep. Lucid dreams are generally thought to arise from non-lucid dreams in REM sleep (Stephen LaBerge, 1986).‚Äú

----Best experienced in full screen----

Probabilities;

- Unique preview features (exclusive for preview image)

- Generative color palette

- 2 different light styles

- 4 different interaction animation styles 

- Some unique features

This piece is using shaders thus results may be different from device to device.

You can press 's' in liveMode to save the current state as .png.

Half of the primary sales go to the Processing Foundation.

Made with p5js and openGL shaders.
@distcollective, November 2022

metadata.name: Play with lines #3 #44
metadata.description:
Life starts from a point
Dots become lines in union
And the lines make our world


Play with lines
This collection is the result of my play with the lines I drew with the tablet in an unbalanced state of mind.
And combining these lines with digital paintings in the background
This collection has 5 layers
The first layer contains oil paintings as a background
The second layer of hatches
The third layer of the lines I have drawn with the tablet is 25 different images
The fourth layer of different covers
The fifth layer of the box and signature

metadata.name: Lemon Princess #181
metadata.description:
After accidentally swigging from a potion of banishment (mistaking it for her moon mead) at the Annual Wizard‚Äôs Gala, Lemon Princess was instantly transformed into a colorful and rapidly modulating energy node.

For a few short moments her karmic fabric strained against extinction. It summoned every possible objection and gripped every precious memory, but alas the brew was too potent and the Princess winked out of existence never to be seen again.

To view each of Lemon Princess' final moments in context (& export them as GIFS) visit:

https://presstube.com/lemon-princess

metadata.description:
Abstract artwork that generates urban-like structures viewed from the sky.

@VolatileMoods, May, 2022.

metadata.name: Patches #101
metadata.description:
This token generates a colorful abstract artwork that appears as watercolor on fabric. Project began as exploration of palettes used in famous masterpieces listed on Color Lisa web site. 97 color combinations used by great artists are applied here on abstract art.

Each piece is generated by bio inspired cellular automata in which colors from chosen palette are competing for domination on canvas. There are three different configurations of space fragmentation and each one is producing specific style.

metadata.name: Annum #8508
metadata.description:
This project is being released in celebration of the 1 year aniversary of Achromat, my first release on fxhash. In addition to being inspired by Achromat, aspects of other previous projects have been incorporated. My deepest gratitude to all who have collected my work over the past year.

In live mode, add &size=<YOUR_PIXEL_SIZE> to change the pixel size of the image for export (Right click to save). For example, &size=4000 will set the width of the image to be 4000 pixels.

50% of primary sales go to Savepakistan.

metadata.description:

There are 103 color sets, 3 frame, 4 fragment and 2 dyeing types.

metadata.name: F.T.B.A #32
metadata.description:
https://rhaegarart.com/f-t-b-a/

A generative art that tries to express the difference between reality and unreality.

This project is coded in an optimized way. The main code is written with just 36 lines of code. The total js code with fxFeatures is 61 lines.

Features:

- 2 Background styles: Dark & Bright
- 4 Texture intensities: Low-Medium-High-Very High
- 3 Noise complexities: Low-Medium-High
- 4 Noise amounts: Low-Medium-High-Very High
- 2 Noise positions: Over the cuts & Beyond the Cuts
- 4 Cut intensities: Low-Medium-High-Very High
- 13 Cut styles: Youth-Imagination-Tale-Onion-Family-Wood-Library-Chocolate-Gate-Tradition-Lake-Reflection-Paper
- 3 Cut width: Low-Medium-High
- 28 Different color palettes
- 2 Different color directions

Warning! Loading might take up to 40 seconds as your machine's power. Also, your browser might not respond during the loading stage. Please be patient till the end.

The project was tested on desktop Chrome 106.0.5249.119, Mozilla 105.0.3, and Edge 106.0.1370.42 versions.

Press 's' to export a high-res png file in live mode.

Made with p5js and WebGL shaders.

CC BY-NC-SA 4.0 LICENSE

November 2022 / Rhaegar
